l Hill Middle School, September 29, 2011</ref>\n\nIn 2011, Drexel Hill Middle School declined to Warning status.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://paayp.emetric.net/School/Overview/c23/125239452/1971 |title=Drexel Hill Middle School AYP Overview AYP Overview 2011 |author=Pennsylvania Department of Education |date=September 29, 2011 |access-date=2012-08-09 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120928073828/http://paayp.emetric.net/School/Overview/c23/125239452/1971 |archive-date=2012-09-28 |url-status=dead }}</ref> In 2010, Drexel Hill Middle School achieved AYP status under No Child Left Behind.\n\n;'''PSSA Results: '''\n{{col-begin}}\n{{col-1-of-2}}\n'''8th Grade Reading'''\n*2011 - 80% on grade level (9% below basic). State - 81.8%<ref>{{cite web |url=http://paayp.emetric.net/Content/reportcards/RC11S125239452000001971.PDF |title=Drexel Hill Middle School Academic Achievement Report Card 2011 |author=Pennsylvania Department of Education |date=September 29, 2011 }}{{Dead link|date=September 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>\n*2010 - 80% (8% below basic). State - 81%\n*2009 - 79% (9% below basic), State - 80%\n*2008 - 75% (11% below basic), State - 78%\n*2007 - 75% (11% below basic), State - 75%\n{{col-2-of-2}}\n'''8th Grade Math:'''\n*2011 - 74% on grade level (12% below basic). State - 76.9%\n*2010 - 76% (10% below basic). State - 75%\n*2009 - 67% (10% below basic). State - 71%\n*2008 - 69% (17% below basic). State - 70%\n*2007 - 63% (19% below basic). State - 68%\n{{col-end}}\n\n'''8th Grade Science:'''\n*2011 - 56% on grade level (24% below basic). State \u2013 58.3% of 8th graders were on grade level.\n*2010 - 56% (24% below basic). State \u2013 57%\n*2009 - 50% (23% below basic). State - 55%\n*2008 - 45% (24% below basic). State - 52%\n*2007 - tested, but results not made public.\n\n{{col-begin}}\n{{col-1-of-2}}\n'''7th Grade Reading'''\n*2011 - 73% on grade level (12% below basic). State \u2013 76%\n*2010 - 71% (10% below basic). State - 